<paragraph id="IAS38_110" base="SL32739" principles="no"><paranum>110</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 38"/><data name="paranum" value="110"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS38_P0301">In accordance with <xref id="IAS38_X0325" base="F16456314" href="../ias36/IAS36_TOC0001.dita#IAS36_TOC0001">IAS 36</xref>, reassessing the <xref base="SL141720" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0075">useful life<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0380"/></ph></xref> of an <xref base="SL141716" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0070">intangible asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0193"/></ph></xref> as finite rather than indefinite is an indicator that the asset may be impaired. As a result, the entity tests the asset for impairment by comparing its recoverable amount, determined in accordance with <xref id="IAS38_X0326" base="F16456315" href="../ias36/IAS36_TOC0001.dita#IAS36_TOC0001">IAS 36</xref>,  with its carrying amount, and recognising any excess of the <xref base="SL141709" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0063">carrying amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0026"/></ph></xref> over the recoverable amount as an <xref base="SL141715" href="IAS38_8.dita#IAS38_8/IAS38_P0069">impairment loss<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0176"/></ph></xref>.</p></body></paragraph>